cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a framework for training classifiers using natural language explanations. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper involves developing a semantic parser to convert natural language explanations into programmatic labeling functions. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper discusses training classifiers using unlabeled data. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper involves relation extraction tasks. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the use of labeling functions to generate noisy labels for training classifiers.
